cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically semantic segmentation, which falls under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper deals with the problem of occlusion, which is a common challenge in robotics and autonomous systems, making cs.RO (Robotics) a likely sub-category as well. The use of deep neural networks also suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible sub-category. The paper also proposes a modification to the standard cross-entropy loss, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the validation of the results on a newly generated dataset suggests that cs.GR (Graphics) could also be a relevant sub-category.
